<p>I want to make my website be able to show a tree structure of links when a user searches it through Google.</p>  <p>I've used sitemap to generate the structure:</p>  <pre><code># Set the host name for URL creation SitemapGenerator::Sitemap.default_host = "https://lazyair.co"  SitemapGenerator::Sitemap.create do   add '/about-us', :changefreq =&gt; 'weekly'   add '/contact_us', :changefreq =&gt; 'weekly'   add '/tutorial', :changefreq =&gt; 'weekly'   add '/user', :changefreq =&gt; 'daily' end </code></pre>  <h1>Expected  format</h1>  <p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/DmCQtFim.png" alt=""></p>  <h1>Current  format</h1>  <p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/fzSFtrHm.png" alt=""></p>